description:
High-rise business hotel steps from Gare Montparnasse

Left Bank transport hub
The high-rise, modern Pullman Paris Montparnasse hotel places you 2 blocks from Gare Montparnasse, a major rail station in Paris's 14th arrondissement. The relatively quiet, non-touristy feel of this Left Bank location suits business travelers and those looking for less bustle.

Bohemian charm
Once the stomping ground of authors and painters like Hemingway, Beckett, and Picasso, Montparnasse still feels artsy and bohemian. You can people-watch in popular cafs like La Rotonde, or be inspired by the beautiful views from Tour Montparnasse, a 5-minute walk away.

Business and pleasure
The Pullman Montparnasse is popular with business travelers, with large meeting spaces and 900-plus guestrooms along with banqueting facilities. There is a restaurant and bar in the hotel, but most guests opt to eat at the plentiful neighborhood cafs.

Rooms with a view
Guestrooms on higher floors offer panoramic views of Paris some look towards the Eiffel Tower. The large rooms (by Paris standards) are uncluttered, with satellite LCD TVs and comfortable beds. All rooms have free WiFi.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
The 25-floor Pullman Paris Montparnasse provides a computer connectivity lounge, secretarial services, a gift shop, a newsstand, and a well-staffed concierge desk. WiFi is complimentary. Child care and supervised activities for children are offered for an additional charge.

The Pullman Paris Montparnasse is a smoke-free property.

DINING.value:
JUST IN - Contemporary, artistic decor complements the innovative French cuisine at this venue, open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner Monday through Friday. This restaurant overlooks the garden and offers colorful, tasty lunchtime buffets. In the evening, the chef creates an inventive array of dishes using carefully selected products from within a 125-mile (200-kilometer) radius.

Opening hours: 7 AM-10:30 AM/Noon until 10:30 PM

Caf Atlantic - This friendly venue is the perfect place to have a drink, meal, or business meeting. Breakfast, lunch, and dinner are served, as well as drinks and afternoon tea. A selection of snacks and drinks from the Atlantic Express is available for take away.
Opening hours: 6:30 AM-2 PM

Room service is available 24 hours a day.

Breakfast is served 6:30 AM-10:30 AM.

RECREATION.value:
Bowling lanes, bicycle rental, and a large fitness club are all within 2 blocks of the hotel in the Montparnasse neighborhood. The elevated Jardin Atlantique across the street has a popular jogging trail. In-line skaters can join thousands of Parisians for a three-hour night tour of Paris every Friday night, meeting at 10 PM outside the Montparnasse train station.

The recreational activities listed below are available either on site or near the hotel; fees may apply.

GOLD.value: Looking for a large hotel in a handy location? The Pullman Paris Montparnasse is a great option. The neighborhood has plenty of eateries, but you won't need to elbow tourists out of the way in the streets. Transport is great: the Air France shuttle to Orly and Charles de Gaulle airports stops across the street, and rail and metro connections are 2 short blocks away. The free WiFi is a nice perk.

GUESTS_LOVE.value:
Guests Love
  • Proximity to major rail station, Gare Montparnasse, with metro connections

  • Quiet rooms and comfortable beds allow for a good night's sleep

  • Air France shuttle bus to Charles de Gaulle and Orly airports stops across the street

  • Lively neighborhood with plenty of cafs

    • Keep in Mind
  • The elevators can be a little slow to come at times

  • WiFi doesn't work well in all rooms

  • Neighborhood is a little off the tourist track (a plus for some!)

END_OF_THE_DAY.value:
At the end of the day
Our guests love the large rooms and comfortable beds at Pullman Paris Montparnasse. Some guests like the untouristy area and numerous eateries; others wish they were closer to the sights. All guests appreciate the proximity to Gare Montparnasse.

ROOM_FEATURE.value: At Pullman Paris Montparnasse, you'll be just a 5-minute drive from Tour Montparnasse and Cartier Foundation for Contemporary Art. Guests can visit the fitness center for a workout or grab a bite to eat at JUST IN, which serves French cuisine and is open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. A bar/lounge and a snack bar/deli are other highlights, and rooms at this upscale hotel offer 24-hour room service and flat-screen TVs.
